  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 17 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 6 critical, 6 high, 12 medium, 15 normal. Key bases needing attention include Sibiu (SBZ/LRSB), Timişoara Traian Vuia (TSR/LRTR) and Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE); plus 9 other bases. 12 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD). Network hotspots: Turku (TKU/EFTU), Ålesund Airport, Vigra (AES/ENAL), Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and 12 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Ålesund Airport, Vigra (AES/ENAL), Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) and 9 others.",
